{
  "id": 5163741220044800,
  "name": "Clipboardchange event - Sticky activation / Permission check",
  "summary": "Require sticky user activation or clipboard-read permission to fire `clipboardchange` events, preventing unauthorized clipboard monitoring.\n\nThis is as per the spec defined here - https://www.w3.org/TR/clipboard-apis/#clipboard-event-clipboardchange\n\nReason for PSA - Clipboardchange event is relatively new (144) and this has minimal web facing change. It is expected that in most cases sticky activation / clipboard-read permission would already be present where clipboard monitoring is done (like remote desktop clients)",
